      • getCursorOrder

        public Order getCursorOrder()
        Returns:
        Gets the reference to the Order wrapped by the OrderListNode currently referenced by cursor. Returns the reference by the Order wrapped by the OrderListNode currently referenced by cursor. If the cursor is null, then this method should return null as well (i.e.the cursor does not reference an Order).

      • resetCursorToHead

        public void resetCursorToHead()
        Returns the cursor to the start of the list.
        Postconditions If head is not null, the cursor now references the first OrderListNode in this list. If head is null, the cursor is set to null as well (there are no Orders in this list).

      • resetCursorToTail

        public void resetCursorToTail()
        Sets the cursor to the end of the list.
        Postconditions If tail is not null, the cursor now references the last OrderListNode in this list. If tail is null, the cursor is set to null as well.

      • cursorForward

        public void cursorForward()
                   throws EndOfListException
        Moves the cursor to select the next OrderListNode in the list.
        Preconditions the cursor cannot be at the tail
        Postconditions the cursor has moved one node forward in the linked list
        Throws:
        EndOfListException - if cursor is at the tail of the list, or if cursor and tail are both null.

      • cursorBackward

        public void cursorBackward()
                    throws EndOfListException
        Moves the cursor to select the previous OrderListNode in the list.
        Preconditions the cursor cannot be at the head
        Postconditions the cursor has moved one node backward in the linked list
        Throws:
        EndOfListException - if cursor is at the head of the list, or if cursor and head are both null.

      • cut

        public Order cut()
          throws EndOfListException
        cuts the node at cursor, saves the data to cutNode and then removes it from the list
        Preconditions the cursor cannot null
        Postconditions the OrderListNode referenced by cursor has been removed from the list All other OrderListNodes in the list exist in the same order as before. The cursor now references the previous OrderListNode (or the head, if the cursor previously referenced the head of the list).
        Returns:
        returns an Order object that is saved in cutNode
        Throws:
        EndOfListException - if cursor is null

      • removeCursor

        public Order removeCursor()
                   throws EndOfListException
        Removes the OrderListNode referenced by cursor and returns the Order inside.
        Preconditions cursor is not null.
        Postconditions The OrderListNode referenced by cursor has been removed from the list. All other OrderListNodes in the list exist in the same order as before. The cursor now references the previous OrderListNode (or the head, if the cursor previously referenced the head of the list).
        Returns:
        removedNodeData, which is the Order data saved in the OrderListNode that is being removed
        Throws:
        EndOfListException - if cursor is null

      • paste

        public void paste(Order clipboard)
           throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        creates an OrderListnode from the Order data in clipboard and and adds it to the list
        Preconditions clipboard is not null.
        Postconditions The Order referenced by clipboard wrapped in an OrderListNode and added to the list. If there cursor is not null, node added after cursor. If the cursor is null and the list is empty then the new node will be the head, tail and cursor.
        Parameters:
        clipboard - this is the Order object that will be wrapped by OrderListNode
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if clipboard is null

      • insertAfterSimilar

        public void insertAfterSimilar(Order newOrder)
                        throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Inserts the indicated Order after the a similar order in the list.
        Preconditions newOrder is not null
        Postconditions newOrder has been wrapped in a new OrderListNode object. If the order name and price match, an order already in the list is considered a smiliar order. The newOLN will be added after that existing order. If there is no similar order, newOLN is simply appended to the tail.
        Parameters:
        newOrder - takes in Order data to wrap in an OrderListNode and add to the list
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if newOrder is null.

      • insertAfterCursor

        public void insertAfterCursor(Order newOrder)
                       throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Inserts the indicated Order after the cursor.
        Preconditions newOrder is not null
        Postconditions newOrder has been wrapped in a new OrderListNode object. If cursor was previously not null, the newly created OrderListNode has been inserted into the list after the cursor. If cursor was previously null, the newly created OrderListNode has been set as the new head of the list (as well as the tail). The cursor now references the newly created OrderListNode.
        Parameters:
        newOrder - takes in Order data to wrap in an OrderListNode and add to the list
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if newOrder is null.

      • appendToTail

        public void appendToTail(Order newOrder)
                  throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Inserts the indicated Order after the tail of the list.
        Preconditions newOrder is not null
        Postconditions newOrder has been wrapped in a new OrderListNode object. If tail was previously not null, the newly created OrderListNode has been inserted into the list after the tail. If tail was previously null, the newly created OrderListNode has been set as the new head of the list (as well as the tail and the cursor). The tail now references the newly created OrderListNode. Note: This insertion method does not affect the cursor, unless the list was previously empty. In that case, head, tail, and cursor should all reference the new OrderListNode.
        Parameters:
        newOrder -
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if newOrder is null.

      • appendToHead

        public void appendToHead(Order newOrder)
                  throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Inserts the indicated Order after the head of the list.
        Preconditions newOrder is not null
        Postconditions newOrder has been wrapped in a new OrderListNode object. If the head was null, the new node is now the head, tail and cursor. If head was not null, the new order is now the head, which is linked to the node was that was the head
        Parameters:
        newOrder - takes in an Order object to wrap and add
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - [if the new Order parameter is null, then the exception is thrown since we can't have a null node or null reference in the list]

        prints the table of order data to the console
